 =顧炎武 (1613-1682)=
==Works==
* 日知錄
* 音學五書 printed 1667, also called 《音统》， includes 音論三卷，詩本音十卷，易音三卷，唐韻正二十卷，古音表二卷
* [[金石文字記]] printed ~1695 in 顧亭林先生遺書十種 (abbr.: 亭林十種)
==Literature==
===PhD Dissertations===
* Weiying Ku: The political theories of Ku Yen-wu and the manchu conquest, The University of British Columbia, 1983
* I-fan Ch'eng: Development and frustrations of statecraft in mid-Ming China: As reflected in the experiences of the Gu family of Jiangnan during the sixteenth century, University of California Berkeley, 1988
* John Patrick Delury: Despotism above and below: Gu Yanwu's "Record of Daily Learning" on power, money, and mores, Yale University, 2007
===Articles===
* Willard J. Peterson: "The Life of Ku Yen-wu (1613-1682), Harvard Journal of Asiatic Studies, Volume 28, 1968, pp. 114-156 [[@http://www.jstor.org/stable/2718597|JSTOR]] 
* Willard J. Peterson: "The Life of Ku Yen-wu (1613-1682), Harvard Journal of Asiatic Studies, Volume 29, 1969, pp. 201-247 [[@http://www.jstor.org/stable/2718835|JSTOR]] 
* Fang Chao-Ying: "Ku Yan-wu", in Arthur W. Hummel: Eminent Chinese of the Ch'ing period [清代名人传略] (1644 - 1912). Washington: United States Government Printing Office, 1943-1944. PP. 421-426
